de.uka.ipd.sdq.beagle.core.evaluableexpressions.util

Class EvaluableExpressionSimplifier

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.uka.ipd.sdq.beagle.core.evaluableexpressions.util.ModifyingEvaluableExpressionVisitor
      • de.uka.ipd.sdq.beagle.core.evaluableexpressions.util.EvaluableExpressionSimplifier

  • public class EvaluableExpressionSimplifier
extends ModifyingEvaluableExpressionVisitor
    Produces shorter versions of unnecessarily complex EvaluableExpressions. The class aims to reduce the number of an expressions’s inner expressions on a best effort basis. It does not guarantee that it will find the shortest version. In other words, if |e| describes the number of e’s inner expressions, this.simplify(e) will return an expression e1, such that |e1| ≤ |e| and for any EvaluableVariableAssignment x e.evaluate(x) = e1.evaluate(x).
